                >
                  <p>
                    <span
                      class="description-title"
                      style="font-size: 80px; font-weight: 800"
                      >What is Self-Worth?
                    </span>
                  </p>
                </div>
                <div class="content ps-0 ps-lg-5">
                  <p class="fst-italic">
                    Self-worth is the intrinsic value we assign to ourselves as
                    human beings. It reflects our belief in our own value,
                    independent of external validation. This intrinsic value is
                    fundamental; it influences our decisions, relationships, and
                    aspirations. If we lack confidence in our self-worth, we may
                    find it challenging to commit to goals or visions larger
                    than ourselves. In such cases, we often seek validation and
                    acceptance from others to feel worthy.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-lg-12" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="250">
              <div
                class="aboutcontainer"
                style="box-shadow: rgba(99, 99, 99, 0.2) 0px 2px 8px 0px"
              >
                <div
                  class="container section-title"
                  style="padding-bottom: 1px; margin-top: 0px"
                  data-aos="fade-up"
                >
                  <p>
                    <span
                      class="description-title"
                      style="font-size: 80px; font-weight: 800"
                      >The Nature of Self-Esteem
                    </span>
                  </p>
                </div>
                <div class="content ps-0 ps-lg-5">
                  <p class="fst-italic">
                    In contrast, self-esteem is how we feel about ourselves at
                    any given moment. It can be high or low, depending on
                    various factors, including our achievements, relationships,
                    and internal dialogues. However, it’s important to remember
                    that self-esteem should not be solely based on our outcomes
                    or accomplishments. Our worth is not defined by what we do
                    but by who we are.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="col-lg-12" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="250">
              <div
                class="aboutcontainer"
                style="box-shadow: rgba(99, 99, 99, 0.2) 0px 2px 8px 0px"
              >
                <div
                  class="container section-title"
                  style="padding-bottom: 1px; margin-top: 0px"
                  data-aos="fade-up"
                >
                  <p>
                    <span
                      class="description-title"
                      style="font-size: 80px; font-weight: 800"
                    >
                      The Trap of External Validation
                    </span>
                  </p>
                </div>
                <div class="content ps-0 ps-lg-5">
                  <p class="fst-italic">
                    When we base our self-worth on external achievements, we may
                    end up on a never-ending quest for approval. This reliance
                    on validation can lead to feelings of inadequacy and low
                    self-esteem. A person struggling with low self-esteem might
                    believe they are not enough, leading them to chase
                    perfection or excellence. However, perfection is often an
                    unrealistic goal that can seem miles away, especially when
                    feeling worthless.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-lg-12" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="250">
              <div
                class="aboutcontainer"
                style="box-shadow: rgba(99, 99, 99, 0.2) 0px 2px 8px 0px"
              >
                <div
                  class="container section-title"
                  style="padding-bottom: 1px; margin-top: 0px"
                  data-aos="fade-up"
                >
                  <p>
                    <span
                      class="description-title"
                      style="font-size: 80px; font-weight: 800"
                      >A Shift in Perspective
                    </span>
                  </p>
                </div>
                <div class="content ps-0 ps-lg-5">
                  <p class="fst-italic">
                    Instead of striving for perfection, we can shift our focus
                    to becoming better than we were yesterday. This approach
                    promotes growth and improvement. Every small step towards
                    bettering ourselves contributes to a sense of accomplishment
                    and boosts our self-esteem. By committing to daily
                    improvement, we empower ourselves to recognize our intrinsic
                    worth.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-lg-12" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="250">
              <div
                class="aboutcontainer"
                style="box-shadow: rgba(99, 99, 99, 0.2) 0px 2px 8px 0px"
