                    </span>
                  </p>
                </div>
                <div class="content ps-0 ps-lg-5">
                  <p class="fst-italic">
                    In summary, self-worth is about recognizing our intrinsic
                    value, while self-esteem is about how we feel about
                    ourselves. By understanding that our worth is not contingent
                    on external factors, we can foster a healthier self-image.
                    Embrace the journey of self-improvement, not for the sake of
                    perfection, but for the joy of becoming a better version of
                    yourself. As you focus on giving and adding value to others,
                    your self-worth and self-esteem will naturally grow.
                    Remember, every step forward is a choice towards a more
                    fulfilling life.
                  </p>
